⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Tenar (Arha)
node U1 · U1 · ⟦Tenar (Arha):U1:cbd45b⟧

WHO   — Tenar (Arha) — the Eaten One · the priestess who chose her own name
WHAT  — The keeper of the Undertomb who turned from the service of unmaking — first Arha, then Tenar, then Goha the widow and farmwife who would one day be called by dragons.
WHERE — U1 · Le Guin  Framework inputs: Earthsea  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because to be Eaten is to be hollowed for the dark; because freedom is the harder thing than power; because the choice to live, to love, to keep a farm and raise a child is no smaller than the choice to be Archmage.
HOW   — By guarding the Ring of Erreth-Akbe in the labyrinth's dark, by trusting the thief Ged enough to walk out of the only world she knew, and by taking back the name the Tombs had eaten.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  They ate my name in the dark; in the dark a man gave it back — and I walked out into the light by my own choosing.

spoken token : brux-nis-graern   ·   hex : cbd45b
